TopicTitle: Lunar impact site of Apollo 16 SIVB found

Articles.Content:
The Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter spotted the crater formed by the Apollo 16 SIVB booster on impact, after several years of searching.

http://www.nasa.gov/image-feature/goddard/lro-finds-apollo-16-booster-rocket-impact-site

Thanks for linking to that!

I was fascinated how rectangular the crater was. I guess the stage hit the surface almost exactly side-on?
